    ("All four specs cite their doctrine memory + prior spec sources. No fabricated concepts. Every design decision traces to either Alfred verbatim, the R7RS-small standard, the identity-slat-rosetta-compat-architecture doctrine, or the existing MOTOI-SCHEME-REFERENCE-SCHEMA."
     "Every SLAT ships with its MD twin per the durable-feedback rule (SLAT canonical, MD rendered for readers who can't parse SLAT)."
     "Zero code changes. Zero commits. All eight files are new drafts in ~/code/motoi-scheme/spec/. Alfred reviews before anything downstream depends on them."
     "Zero touching of ~/.forge/runs/motoi-4.0/ or any Motoi 4.0 training artifact."
     "Terminology is 'variant' throughout (per variant-not-dialect-terminology-2026-07-19). No 'dialect' references except in citations to older files."
     "The R7RS-SMALL primitive floor SLAT uses the phrase 'floor-eligible-because' on every primitive — this makes the floor auditable, not just declared. A future automated audit can grep for missing or vague reasons."
     "The virtual shape vocabulary is DELIBERATELY small (14 kinds). Growing it requires doctrine memory + cosign. This keeps the compat contract stable."))

